- Problem Statement : Given a file sorted element written inside it after first 8 byte in 
		      first 8 bytes contains details of the block size and element size and number of element
		      byte level access can not be done in m2 only a block size memory can be fetch 
		      Write a code to perform searching on given data such minimum access of M2 should be taken
		      use of m1 memory which will be very less in size compared to M2 is allowed only
		      first fetch block in M1 to gain byte level acces to data
- User Interface :
        -- input shall be in the file
        -- each element is of size 4 byte can't be changed since int is used to read data element 
        -- Block Size : always in 2 to the power k  
        -- Memory indexing scheme :
                --- Bytes : Numbered from left to right 
                            Starting from 0 and ending on (n - 1)
                        +---------------------------------------------+
                        | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | |
                        +---------------------------------------------+
                         0 1 2 ...                                   n-1 = 2048

                --- Bits : Numbered from rigth to left starting from 0 and ending on 7
                        +---------------+
                        | | | | | | | | |
                        +---------------+
                         7 6 5 4 3 2 1 0

        -- In the program Input is given inside the file
        -- User can  write anything in last bytes i.e. from where given data ends -----Assume enought space is there
        -- Program should search given numbers and tell if it exists or not


Files:-

Write_data.c :- This file writes the given number of elements in file name new
parameters to be set

#define num_of_elements (513 ) //tell number of elements
#define element_size 4  //its fixed
#define block 32 //block sized only care should be that m1 could hold atleast two blocks

/////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
set_block.c :- Need to set Block size and elment size and tell element count for searching and abstraction to be created

B_size=32; //store block size of m2
E_size=4; //store elements size in each block
E_cnt=513;  //store total given elements count

/////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

search_file.c :- Createst the abtraction of given blocks at the end file named "new" and perform seaching on that for number of elements times
		 for random numbers and print number and its status in form of 0 and 1
		 0 for non-present number
		 1 for present number

///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

print.c :- print the written numbers of m2
binsearch :- It contains logic for serching element it is include in file search_file.c

///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
Run :- just runs the above file in sequence and store result in file name "result"
gcc write.c
./a.out
gcc search_file.c
./a.out > result



